<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="span">Conduct a Healthcare Risk Assessment</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1004" relname="span">Covered entities under the U.S. Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="2" relname="restatement">( HIPAA )</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="elaboration">of 1996 ,</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1005" relname="span">are health plans , healthcare clearinghouses , and any healthcare provider</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="5" relname="elaboration">who transmits health information in an electronic form .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1008" relname="span">Covered entities need to comply with the HIPAA Privacy and Security Rules</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="purpose">in order to avoid penalties .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="span">One of the Security Rule ’s main requirements is the performance of a risk analysis .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1012" relname="attribution">The Security Rule stipulates</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1012" relname="contrast">that a risk analysis should be documented</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="contrast">but it does n’t require any specific format for it .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1013" relname="span">This article will present several steps</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="13" relname="elaboration">of how to conduct a proper healthcare risk assessment .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Define the Scope of the Risk Analysis .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">There are different types of risk analysis methods</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="17" relname="elaboration">depending on its scope .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="span">The scope of the healthcare risk assessment includes the potential risks and vulnerabilities to the confidentiality , availability and integrity of all ePHI</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="19" relname="elaboration">that a covered entity creates , receives , maintains , or transmits .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Gather Current Documentation .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1016" relname="sequence">A covered entity should gather and document information on where ePHI is stored , maintained and transmitted .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">This can be done</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="span">by checking current and past projects ,</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="24" relname="elaboration">auditing documents .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Identify Potential Threats and Vulnerabilities .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">This step is essential</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="purpose">to determining the level of risk .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1031" relname="span">All anticipated threats</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="elaboration">( natural , environmental or human )</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1030" relname="joint">and vulnerabilities should be documented in category lists</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1030" relname="joint">and analyzed afterwards .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Analyze Current Security Measures .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1036" relname="span">All security measures</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="34" relname="elaboration">that a covered entity uses</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1036" relname="purpose">to protect ePHI should be documented .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Security measures can be divided into technical</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1016" relname="sequence">– related to the software and hardware in the network -</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="span">and non-technical –</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="elaboration">related to management and operations .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1016" relname="sequence">This step will reveal whether the covered entity has enough security safeguards in place .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Determine the Likelihood and Impact of Threats .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1044" relname="span">The covered entity has to analyze each threat and vulnerability combination</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1045" relname="span">in order to determine the probability</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="44" relname="elaboration">a threat can occur .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="contrast">The likelihood of threat occurrence can be defined as low , medium and high</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1047" relname="contrast">or can be a numeric representation .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">The threat impact should also be defined</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="means">by using a similar rating system .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Determine the Risk Level .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1052" relname="span">Make a risk level matrix</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="51" relname="means">using the identified likelihood and threat impact .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Choose a rating system such as the low , medium and high rating system .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1055" relname="span">Add an action description to each risk level ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="span">which will clarify to management</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="span">what actions should be taken</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="purpose">to prevent or minimize this risk and when .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Identify New Security Measures .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1061" relname="circumstance">After identifying the risk level ,</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1062" relname="attribution">covered entities have to think</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="span">what security measures need to be taken</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="purpose">to reduce risks .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="64" relname="circumstance">When defining new security measures ,</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="span">it is important to take into account factors such as the measures ’ effectiveness , legislative or regulatory requirements and other organization ’s policies .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Like each of the previous steps ,</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1016" relname="sequence">this step should also be diligently documented .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="preparation">Video</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="span">EPHI can be found in various electronic media</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="span">so covered entities should consider all forms of media</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="70" relname="elaboration">containing ePHI in their analysis .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1073" relname="span">Examples of such media are hard drives , floppy disks , CDs , DVDs , smart cards , personal digital assistants</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="72" relname="elaboration">( PDA ) ,</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1072" relname="same_unit">transmission media , and portable electronic storage media .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1074" relname="sequence">Take into account all possible threat outcomes .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1075" relname="same_unit">The most common impacts as a result of exploited vulnerabilities</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1075" relname="same_unit">are loss or corruption of ePHI , disclosure or unavailability of ePHI , loss of software or hardware inventory , and loss of reputation .</segment>
